  "term_display": "Token Tax",
  "stratum": "author-coinage",
  "canonical_definition": "Token Tax names the explicit token-overhead cost a structured notation pays in exchange for structural integrity, auditability, and reasoning headroom — reframing that overhead from \"waste\" to \"tax\": a price paid for benefits (line-oriented partial-validity, type enforcement, freed reasoning budget, audit-grade provenance) that block-format brevity does not deliver.",
  "near_neighbors": [
    "token cost / API cost-per-token",
    "bloat / overhead",
